{"paperId": "fe33be95849c556ce0bdffaa1d2c7db9bb2e2c61", "abstract": "We introduce RecurrentGemma, an open language model which uses Google's novel Griffin architecture. Griffin combines linear recurrences with local attention to achieve excellent performance on language. It has a fixed-sized state, which reduces memory use and enables efficient inference on long sequences. We provide a pre-trained model with 2B non-embedding parameters, and an instruction tuned variant. Both models achieve comparable performance to Gemma-2B despite being trained on fewer tokens.", "venue": "arXiv.org", "year": 2024, "citationCount": 9, "influentialCitationCount": 2, "openAccessPdf": null, "tldr": {"model": "tldr@v2.0.0", "text": null}, "embedding": {"model": "specter_v2", "vector": [0.021269124001264572, 0.4995839595794678, -0.7781177759170532, 0.17750641703605652, -0.12350278347730637, -0.3105951249599457, 0.9857803583145142, -0.05327751860022545, -0.2822544574737549, -0.2992878258228302, 0.8129295706748962, -0.5730351805686951, 1.0026476383209229, 0.07041127979755402, -0.3364770710468292, 0.32425978779792786, -0.9659683704376221, -0.24507459998130798, 0.08012017607688904, -0.426843523979187, 0.13545851409435272, -0.6266136169433594, -1.2741081714630127, 0.11425434798002243, 0.12610052525997162, 0.42284196615219116, 0.11227284371852875, 0.8852553963661194, -0.46709489822387695, 0.7980273365974426, 0.47771725058555603, -0.23874317109584808, -0.05217531695961952, 0.19658097624778748, -0.6275648474693298, -0.5432961583137512, 0.36981573700904846, -0.3353528678417206, -0.5001684427261353, 0.6050263047218323, -0.3715520203113556, 0.3951788544654846, 0.36686941981315613, -0.6234946846961975, -0.24595391750335693, 0.9573206901550293, 0.4255344271659851, 0.8899149298667908, -0.3162398636341095, -0.3920917809009552, 1.582626461982727, -1.2456395626068115, 0.44767922163009644, 1.094454050064087, 0.27636051177978516, 0.3883249759674072, -0.09196341782808304, -0.5175849199295044, 1.07599568367